  <data name="FAQTitle" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Frequently Asked Questions about MedZapis</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ1Question" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Is MedZapis paid for patients?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ1Answer" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Online registration through MedZapis is free for patients. You only pay for the appointment with the doctor or clinic you choose. MedZapis does not charge any additional commission from patients and does not interfere with prices.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ2Question" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Do I need to download an app?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ2Answer" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>No. MedZapis works like a regular website. You can also install it as an app using the "Add to Home Screen" function in your mobile browser.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ3Question" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>What does MedZapis offer for doctors?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ3Answer" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>For doctors, MedZapis is a small online office: a unified calendar of appointments, patient list, and simple statistics. This helps plan the workday, track registrations, and reduce no-shows.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ4Question" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Who is responsible for medical care?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ4Answer" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Responsibility for the quality and content of medical care lies directly with the doctor or clinic.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ5Question" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How secure is my data?</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FAQ5Answer" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>We only collect the minimum data necessary for registration. Data is transmitted through encrypted channels and stored on secure servers.</value>
  </data>
